
@startuml

' Define classes
class Contract {
  - contractID: String
  - dateSigned: Date
  - legalTerms: String
  - deliveryConditions: String
  + manageSalesperson(salesperson: Salesperson)
  + addAcquisition(acquisition: Acquisition)
}

class Salesperson {
  - salespersonID: String
  - name: String
  - contactInfo: String
  + assignToContract(contract: Contract)
  + changeContract(contract: Contract, newSalesperson: Salesperson)
}

class Acquisition {
  - acquisitionID: String
  - model: String
  - price: Double
  - options: String
  - deliveryDate: Date
  + getDetails(): String
}

class AirlineCompany {
  - companyID: String
  - name: String
  - parentCompany: AirlineCompany
  + hasDaughterCompany(): Boolean
}

' Relationships
Contract "1" -- "0..*" Acquisition : consists of
Contract "1" -- "1" Salesperson : managed by
Salesperson "1" -- "0..*" Contract : manages
AirlineCompany "1" -- "0..*" AirlineCompany : has daughter (parent-child relationship)

@enduml

---

### Explanation of the Diagram:

- **`Contract`**: Represents a contract between Boeing and an airline company. It contains general terms that apply to all acquisitions under this contract.
- **`Salesperson`**: An employee who manages one or more contracts. A salesperson can be assigned to multiple contracts, and they may change over time.
- **`Acquisition`**: Represents a specific airplane purchase within a contract. It includes details like model, price, options, and delivery date.
- **`AirlineCompany`**: Represents an airline company. There's a parent-child relationship between airlines to track mother-daughter company relationships.

This diagram provides a high-level view of the domain model and can be further expanded with additional attributes or methods as needed.